{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Greek ''[[μαθηματικός]]'' (mathematikós), fond of learning, from ''[[μάθημα]]'' (máthema), science, knowledge, learning.

===Noun===
'''mathematics''' ''singular'' (''abbreviation'' '''[[maths]]''' (''British''), '''[[math]]''' (''US''))

# The [[study]] of [[number]]s, [[shape]]s, [[structure]] and [[change]] and the relationships between these concepts.

